    "analysis": "The previous step aggregated metric.csv (no time filtering) into per-(cmdb_id, kpi_name) groups and computed statistics including count, min, max, mean, P50, P90, and P95. The result shows ~68 components and multiple KPI types (cpu, mem, diskio, socket, latency-50/90, error, workload, etc.). Many groups have 25 samples (so the full series length is small and likely covers the incident window). We now need to perform anomaly detection using global thresholds (P95 per group computed from the full series) and then inspect only points inside the incident window to find candidate faulty component-KPIs. The next step should find which (component,KPI) had values inside the incident window that exceeded their global P95 and produce compact aggregates (counts, earliest anomaly timestamp, max value in window, and the P95 threshold) to prioritize candidates for trace/log inspection.",
