}

{
    "analysis": "Trace analysis found short-lived spikes in trace row_count metrics across many services during the incident window (earliest anomalies between ~22:22 and ~22:40 UTC). Metric analysis showed transient memory (mem) KPI breaches across many services clustered around ~22:44 UTC (auth had an earlier mem breach at 22:34). The pattern suggests an upstream traffic surge (trace row_count spikes) followed by transient memory pressure across services. To decide whether memory spikes are root-causal or secondary to traffic bursts, we must inspect logs and error messages for signs of: socket errors, OOM/GC, increased error counts, or network issues. The next step is targeted log analysis for the candidate services that showed metric/trace anomalies.",
